│ The `impliesPoison` function recursively determines whether  │
│ a value (`ValAssumedPoison`) implies poison for another      │
│ value (`V`). It uses helper functions like                   │
│ `isGuaranteedNotToBePoison` and `directlyImpliesPoison` to   │
│ make this determination. The recursion depth is limited to   │
│ prevent infinite loops.                                      │
│                                                              │
│ The transformation in `foldSelectOfBools` that replaces a    │
│ `select` with an `xor` does not currently check for poison   │
│ safety using `impliesPoison`. This omission is likely the    │
│ root cause of the issue, as the transformation may introduce │
│ poison in cases where the original `select` instruction does │
│ not.                                                         │
│                                                              │
│ To fix this, I will propose an edit to include a poison      │
│ safety check using `impliesPoison` before applying the       │
│ transformation. Let me finalize the edit points and provide  │
│ the detailed reasoning.                                      │
