│ m_Deferred(B))))) {                                          │
│   if (!impliesPoison(A, B) && !impliesPoison(B, A))          │
│     return BinaryOperator::CreateXor(A, B);                  │
│ }                                                            │
│ ```                                                          │
│                                                              │
│ 5. **Conclusion**: This fix ensures that the transformation  │
│ is only applied when it is poison-safe, preventing the       │
│ introduction of poison in cases where the original `select`  │
│ instruction is well-defined. This aligns the transformation  │
